abstract: Officials at St Paul’s Cathedral in London say that they will go to court to force the removal of protesters who have camped outside the cathedral for two weeks, demonstrating against economic inequality and corporate greed; famed cathedral has been closed to the public for the first time since World War II.
snippet: Officials at St. Paul’s Cathedral in London said that they would go to court to force the removal of protesters who have camped outside the cathedral.
lead_paragraph: Officials at St. Paul’s Cathedral in London said that they would go to court to force the removal of protesters who have camped outside the cathedral.
